Join us this Thursday for our Rock The Runoff virtual concert. Hosted by @KerryWashington, this is sure to be a night you don’t want to miss. 

Tickets start at $5 and your support will help us make sure that Georgians get out to vote on January 5: https://t.co/45oL1yZOOD https://t.co/vrtLZ6O31m

The voices you know, the story you don’t.

The Bee Gees: How Can You Mend a Broken Heart premieres December 12 on @hbomax and available internationally in select cinemas and on digital download #BeeGeesHBO https://t.co/Qx0zgt2Xzo
🙏🏻 https://t.co/9V5yTTPutZ

A short while ago, @tydollasign found himself once again in the studio— this time alongside @jtimberlake.

The two artists discuss music-making, pandemic-cooking, and Ty’s recently released third album, “Featuring Ty Dolla $ign.” https://t.co/uDcgiFFhhX

As we honor and thank #veterans for their service today, we also congratulate Midshipman First Class Sydney Barber for breaking barriers to become the first Black female brigade commander in @NavalAcademy's 175-year history! 🎖️ #VeteransDay2020
https://t.co/T9SORcj7FV

My grandfather, Walter Abrams, served two tours of duty: World War II and the Korean War. He took pride in defending the ideals of our nation + he believed in fighting for progress at home & abroad. Today, I celebrate all who have served. #VeteransDay2020 #ThankyouforyourService
Sending love to all of the veterans and their families who have served and supported this country. We honor and celebrate you today 🙏🏻
🙏🏻 @staceyabrams https://t.co/8xIc715qt6

Over 91.6 million nationwide requested a mail-in ballot to vote. More mail-in ballots means more time spent counting - because these ballots take longer to process. Let’s be patient, EVERY VOTE MUST BE COUNTED. 🗳@ACLU
#VOTE https://t.co/0qqev5wawR

The NAACP is working with @Lyft to offer free, safe rides to polling stations and registered drop box locations across the U.S from now through Election Day. #RideToVote

Lyft Code: NAACPVOTE2020 https://t.co/2J776ocCqO

Have you already voted? 

There is still time to: 

1. Text 5 friends to vote.
2. Share 866-OUR-VOTE with those who will be voting
3. Phone or text bank
4. Donate to your candidates of choice
5. Share info on @CollectivePAC’s FREE poll rides in swing states
6. Pray (if you do)
I said what I said. #TheBeeGees https://t.co/4lE04VkKcY
🙌🏻 https://t.co/tkWxlOwUdU

.@jtimberlake kicks off the first episode of Apple Music Essentials! Justin and @zanelowe chat about the most iconic songs that shaped Justin’s career. Listen to #Essentials Radio right now on @applemusic: https://t.co/XpzQkohQyB https://t.co/sQMsLNmf1e

Today, in an America that does not denounce white supremacy... this group of young voices right here fighting for equality is more important than ever. @byp100 is an organization that I’m really proud to support. Please watch: https://t.co/E3bVMhfRvS
PLEASE VOTE!!!!!🗳 @morethanavote
Back together again 🙏🏼 @Timbaland https://t.co/NtKQIWUf5g

Today's announcement comes more than six months after Breonna Taylor was shot and killed by Louisville police officers in her own home. 

No officers were charged directly in her death. https://t.co/8cfiVu8Ji5

Florida’s pay-to-vote system stops formerly convicted individuals with fines & fees from voting.
Learn how to help at https://t.co/Lx2hzVjSLY so that everyone can register. @FLRightsRestore #FreeTheVote
😍🙌🏻 https://t.co/jl3QJsYWxi

TOMORROW, All In: The Fight For Democracy arrives on Prime Video. 

Take a look at some of the voter suppression tactics you'll learn more about. #AllInForVoting https://t.co/mNKOWSWDnb

We all made a promise to #NeverForget.

Let’s keep our promise by making the world a better place in remembrance of those lost and injured on 9/11, and the many who rose in service in response to the attacks.

You can help at https://t.co/VAmvDt1sds. #911Day https://t.co/1tI6chypWk

Poll workers like Jayvonne, Lauren, Brittny, Tyler, and Arthur are on the frontlines of democracy. On #NationalPollWorkerRecruitmentDay, we’re teaming up with @PowerThePolls to recruit 250,000 new poll workers this fall.

Join us at https://t.co/ARnEBZmdVu. https://t.co/3CGDaUinOp

Today is the first day of Childhood Cancer Awareness Month. Let's cure childhood cancer. Together. Visit our website to see all the ways you can get involved and celebrate the kids of St. Jude together this month, even if we're apart. https://t.co/pMH7uAoRfD https://t.co/SA0ahuDlxA
BREAKING: We are calling for the immediate resignation of Kenosha Police Chief Daniel Miskinis and Kenosha County Sheriff David Beth.

Four years ago today, Colin Kaepernick refused to stand for the national anthem to protest police brutality and racism. 

Do you understand now? https://t.co/mAlfiUjJmg

“We keep loving this country and this country doesn’t love us back.”

Doc Rivers got emotional while talking about Jacob Blake being shot by police and social injustice. https://t.co/qQI2Ld2DGI

#JakeBlake was shot 7 times in his back by a police officer in front of his three small children after breaking up a fight between two women in his community. 

Text 'Jake' to 55156 NOW to demand the officer is fired & arrested for attempting to murder Jake in broad daylight! https://t.co/y3Vs538f46

This couldn’t come at a better time. @allinthefilm breaks down the very real issue of voter suppression in the U.S... The more informed we are, the more prepared we are to fight for democracy. Directed by @lizgarbus and @misscortes, feat. @staceyabrams 💯 https://t.co/yAhtyyOfIB

To every NBA fan ready to watch playoffs, please take a minute to read this letter and consider our call to action. Black, brown, white, this fight is real and you can’t sit on the sidelines.  @morethanavote #BlackLivesMatter https://t.co/MoXgTWlcGS
2002?? 🤯 In the studio with Marty before I ever recorded a single song for Justified. Learning the craft. #FBF https://t.co/mUO6wauyqt

This morning we ran our first TV ad on Fox & Friends and Morning Joe. We’re telling those in the halls of the White House and Congress, the NRA’s boardroom, and the penthouses of 5th Avenue: young people will determine the nation's future. #OurPower https://t.co/PTghirzYDY
Get up to speed on the unconstitutional crackdown on protesters’ rights. We can’t allow this to continue in Portland — or anywhere else. https://t.co/EclDFfQgwM

Tobias Harris’ media availability today lasted 59 seconds.

He had one message. 

“We want to make sure that Daniel Cameron (Kentucky Attorney General) will arrest the cops & the officers involved with Breonna Taylor’s death and that’s all I got to say.” https://t.co/AxKUDGlcIA

When we protest racism in America, people think we are protesting America itself. Why is that the reaction? Because America was built by men who believed in and benefitted from racism. Plain and simple. 

If we plan to move forward, these confederate monuments must come down. https://t.co/j2IgZ8Nr7D
🙌🏻 https://t.co/5sT8YTlK5N
Said it last week about GA.  This is SYSTEMIC RACISM and OPPRESSION.  So angry man. 😤😤😤 #BlackLivesMatter ✊🏾 #MoreThanaVote 🖐🏾 https://t.co/o9440Ugyzv

🗣 WHO SAID IT WAS A #LOCKDOWN?!? Video and song out now EVERYWHERE! Directed by the goat himself Dave Meyers. Many thanks to my family @jayrock @inglewoodSiR @dominicfike @AndraDayMusic @dumbfoundead!! THE PEOPLE ARE RISING! https://t.co/uUlPuNfXO6 https://t.co/kQvMdnXaL6
.@GovBillLee, please join Virginia and New York and make Juneteenth a paid holiday in Tennessee for state employees. Thank you 🙏🏾

ARREST THE COPS THAT KILLED #BREONNATAYLOR. 

And outlaw “no knock” warrants in every state right after that.
